709
00:55:11,267 --> 00:55:13,228
Oh, God.

710
00:55:13,812 --> 00:55:15,647
[SIGHS]

711
00:55:15,814 --> 00:55:17,983
Now I don't have anything.

712
00:55:54,561 --> 00:55:56,563
[PHONE RINGING]

713
00:56:02,360 --> 00:56:04,779
<i>CHARLES [ON RECORDING]:
You dirty rat. Go ahead and try.</i>

714
00:56:04,946 --> 00:56:06,239
<i>Leave a message at the tone, see?</i>

715
00:56:06,406 --> 00:56:07,449
[MACHINE BEEPS]

716
00:56:07,615 --> 00:56:09,325
MARNIE [ON RECORDING]:
Charlie, <i>it is</i> Marnie.

717
00:56:09,492 --> 00:56:10,994
<i>I haven't heard back
from you all day.</i>

718
00:56:11,286 --> 00:56:15,165
<i>Tonight is the Christmas party. Please
don't forget. Wear your tux. Goodbye.</i>

719
00:56:18,293 --> 00:56:19,627
STACEY [ON RECORDING]:
<i>It's</i> Stacey.

720
00:56:19,794 --> 00:56:22,338
<i>I'm coming by to get Ivana's
ski stuff and shoes after work.</i>

721
00:56:22,547 --> 00:56:25,800
<i>You can leave it by the garage door,
okay? Thanks, Charlie.</i>

722
00:56:25,967 --> 00:56:27,927
[MACHINE BEEPS]

723
00:58:12,073 --> 00:58:14,909
CHARLES:
Alex, what is wrong with this picture?

724
00:58:16,077 --> 00:58:17,912
There you go. My man.

725
00:58:22,333 --> 00:58:24,085
Here. Keep it.

726
00:58:26,087 --> 00:58:28,798
We're in this thing together, Alex,
you and me.

727
00:58:29,257 --> 00:58:33,219
You always take really good care of me.
I really appreciate it. Thank you.

728
00:58:35,930 --> 00:58:37,265
[SIGHS]

729
01:00:28,668 --> 01:00:29,711
[SCOFFS]

730
01:00:44,559 --> 01:00:45,601
[GRUNTS]

731
01:00:46,436 --> 01:00:48,354
MAN:
Hey. Hey.

732
01:00:48,521 --> 01:00:50,773
Hey. Hey, what are you doing?

733
01:00:50,982 --> 01:00:52,817
Oh, hey.

734
01:00:53,860 --> 01:00:56,404
MAN:
Oh, hey, stop, man! Stop!

735
01:00:56,571 --> 01:00:57,780
[G ROANS]

736
01:00:57,947 --> 01:00:59,782
Hey, Bobby, get down here.
I need some help.

737
01:00:59,949 --> 01:01:01,993
This guy just busted the front door.

738
01:01:03,494 --> 01:01:05,496
[ENGINE REVS]

739
01:01:05,663 --> 01:01:06,873
MAN:
Stop. Stop.

740
01:01:07,040 --> 01:01:08,416
[TIRES SCREECH]

741
01:01:08,583 --> 01:01:09,667
Damn it.

742
01:01:14,756 --> 01:01:17,800
MAN:
Hey, stop! Come back here.

743
01:01:19,635 --> 01:01:21,929
Hey! Hey!

744
01:01:25,725 --> 01:01:27,268
[TIRES SCREECH]

745
01:01:27,435 --> 01:01:28,686
Whoa, whoa!

746
01:01:28,853 --> 01:01:30,229
What the fuck!

747
01:01:30,438 --> 01:01:32,815
Really? How about some of that?

748
01:01:35,485 --> 01:01:38,946
MAN: Asshole.
- Taxi. Taxi. Taxi.

749
01:01:40,114 --> 01:01:41,324
Thank you.

750
01:01:43,534 --> 01:01:45,036
[SIGHS]

751
01:01:45,203 --> 01:01:48,289
Hey, man.
Can I buy some drugs from you?

752
01:01:48,623 --> 01:01:51,084
You know where I can get some coke
or some grass?

753
01:01:51,250 --> 01:01:53,461
Heh,no.

754
01:01:53,628 --> 01:01:57,048
But I have a friend who sells caviar.
Beluga, from Russia.

755
01:01:57,215 --> 01:01:59,759
Perfect. Take me there. Yay!

756
01:01:59,926 --> 01:02:01,469
[SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN]

757
01:02:07,350 --> 01:02:09,644
Eight hundred bucks? Wow.

758
01:02:10,478 --> 01:02:11,938
This shit better be good.

759
01:02:12,146 --> 01:02:15,983
It's the best. Beluga from Caspian Sea.
I brought here myself.

760
01:02:16,317 --> 01:02:17,985
Only the best for me, right?

761
01:02:18,152 --> 01:02:19,987
- Heh.
- Only the best, heh.

762
01:02:20,613 --> 01:02:22,824
Hey, oh, here.

763
01:02:24,242 --> 01:02:25,493
Thank you.

764
01:02:27,078 --> 01:02:28,121
[MAN SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN]

765
01:02:29,914 --> 01:02:30,957
[m RUSSIAN]

766
01:02:34,210 --> 01:02:35,253
[MAN SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN]

767
01:02:40,883 --> 01:02:42,260
I want to get drunk.

768
01:02:42,552 --> 01:02:44,137
[SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN]

769
01:02:44,303 --> 01:02:47,390
MAN: You seem like you already are.
- Bullshit.

770
01:02:50,977 --> 01:02:52,019
Mm.

771
01:02:52,854 --> 01:02:54,188
Oh, yeah.

772
01:02:54,355 --> 01:02:56,482
Mm, mm.

773
01:02:56,649 --> 01:02:58,025
Oh, yeah.

774
01:02:58,484 --> 01:03:00,945
- Heh, do you like it?
- Great.

775
01:03:03,114 --> 01:03:05,199
CHARLES:
Exactly. See, you get it.

776
01:03:05,700 --> 01:03:09,662
That's why I'm so mad at her.
She never gave me a chance to explain.

777
01:03:10,371 --> 01:03:13,499
Okay, yeah, yeah. Just keep going.

778
01:03:14,709 --> 01:03:16,210
[SIGHS]

779
01:03:16,377 --> 01:03:18,212
God, I'm an asshole.

780
01:03:21,048 --> 01:03:23,551
What I'm about to do
can never be forgiven.

781
01:03:25,219 --> 01:03:27,388
You're not going to hurt somebody?

782
01:03:27,889 --> 01:03:29,223
Maybe somebody hurt me.

783
01:03:29,599 --> 01:03:31,726
Did you think of that?
Maybe somebody hurt me.

784
01:03:31,893 --> 01:03:32,977
Get out of here!

785
01:03:33,561 --> 01:03:37,857
No, no, heh, ha, ha, look, look.
It's just a headphone.

786
01:03:38,065 --> 01:03:40,485
It's fine. It's fine. Everything's fine.

787
01:03:40,651 --> 01:03:43,821
Just keep going. Here. More vodka?

788
01:04:01,589 --> 01:04:05,134
Here's 100 bucks. I want you to wait
right here. I'll be right back.

789
01:04:05,593 --> 01:04:06,928
Here's more.

790
01:04:19,273 --> 01:04:23,110
[STATIC SOUNDING
OVER RECEIVER]

791
01:04:24,612 --> 01:04:26,948
Fuck. Prickle.

792
01:04:34,163 --> 01:04:36,582
IVANA [OVER RECEIVER]: --taught <i>me
about</i> passion, about truth.

793
01:04:37,416 --> 01:04:40,253
STEPHEN [OVER RECEIVER]: [thought
I'd <i>never be able</i> to-- To <i>feel</i> again.

794
01:04:40,461 --> 01:04:42,129
<i>Then you came into...</i>

795
01:04:44,423 --> 01:04:48,761
<i>And now that you're in my arms
I'm never gonna let you go.</i>

796
01:04:59,480 --> 01:05:01,065
IVANA:
Do you see that?

797
01:05:02,692 --> 01:05:04,860
[OVER RECEIVER]
<i>There's someone outside the...</i>

798
01:05:06,362 --> 01:05:09,156
<i>Outside the window, behind that tree.</i>

799
01:05:10,491 --> 01:05:14,245
<i>Oh, my God.
It's my ex-boyfriend behind that tree.</i>

800
01:05:14,453 --> 01:05:17,498
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

801
01:05:19,584 --> 01:05:20,626
Charlie?

802
01:05:21,460 --> 01:05:22,670
Who is this guy?

803
01:05:23,838 --> 01:05:27,091
- Who am I? Who are you?
- Stephen, go back inside.

804
01:05:27,508 --> 01:05:28,968
So this is time alone?

805
01:05:29,468 --> 01:05:33,180
Act one, scene two.
We're rehearsing, you idiot.

806
01:05:33,389 --> 01:05:35,975
Buddy, she wants you to leave her alone.
We're working.

807
01:05:36,517 --> 01:05:38,519
Are you asking me to kick your ass?

808
01:05:39,145 --> 01:05:41,022
- Oh, my God.
- I studied Wing Chun.

809
01:05:41,188 --> 01:05:43,566
Shut up and just go inside.

810
01:05:48,863 --> 01:05:50,698
What are you doing here?

811
01:05:51,782 --> 01:05:53,409
Trying to find out the truth.

812
01:05:54,035 --> 01:05:56,704
And now I know.
You're going skiing with him.

813
01:05:56,871 --> 01:06:00,166
Are you drunk?
What's with the headphones?

814
01:06:00,791 --> 01:06:02,543
You loved me in the beginning.

815
01:06:03,210 --> 01:06:05,921
Don't you understand?
I don't want to be with you anymore.

816
01:06:06,088 --> 01:06:08,341
And yes, I'm going skiing with Stephen.

817
01:06:08,507 --> 01:06:11,093
- I didn't change.
- That's your problem.

818
01:06:11,927 --> 01:06:15,514
You loved me before
and then you just changed your mind?

819
01:06:15,681 --> 01:06:17,475
I don't know what you want me
to say to you.

820
01:06:17,642 --> 01:06:21,228
You're crazy. You're selfish.
Go away. It's over.

821
01:06:22,855 --> 01:06:28,778
How could you be so sweet to the
toothbrushes and such a bitch to me?

822
01:06:29,570 --> 01:06:31,030
What are you talking about?

823
01:06:34,033 --> 01:06:36,202
You know, Ivana, I was thinking.

824
01:06:37,244 --> 01:06:39,121
It was kind of a sad thought.

825
01:06:41,957 --> 01:06:46,087
I'll meet someone and it won't be you.

826
01:06:46,420 --> 01:06:49,173
And I'll fall in love with her...

827
01:06:49,757 --> 01:06:52,968
...and I'll have kids
and a happy family...

828
01:06:55,429 --> 01:06:57,848
...and then I won't love you
like this anymore.

829
01:06:59,100 --> 01:07:00,976
And I'll miss it.

830
01:07:01,936 --> 01:07:03,938
And I'll miss you.

831
01:07:05,106 --> 01:07:09,610
I can't bear not loving you.

832
01:07:10,945 --> 01:07:11,987
[SIGHS]

833
01:07:12,154 --> 01:07:18,077
It will really be totally over between us.

834
01:07:20,079 --> 01:07:21,122
[SOBS]

835
01:07:24,917 --> 01:07:27,461
And then much later...

836
01:07:30,673 --> 01:07:37,304
...I'll see you again
and you'll have grown older, and I'll be old.

837
01:07:38,431 --> 01:07:40,349
And I won't even care.

838
01:07:41,100 --> 01:07:46,981
You'll just be a wrinkly old lady
with gray hair.

839
01:07:48,149 --> 01:07:50,735
And I won't even care anymore.

840
01:07:54,405 --> 01:07:58,159
I don't want to not love you.

841
01:08:01,620 --> 01:08:02,913
Come here.

842
01:08:05,624 --> 01:08:07,960
I could tell you that I hate you.

843
01:08:09,086 --> 01:08:11,380
That you mean nothing to me.

844
01:08:13,007 --> 01:08:14,967
And part of it's true.

845
01:08:16,927 --> 01:08:18,763
But part of it's not.

846
01:08:21,390 --> 01:08:24,518
Thank you for everything
that you gave me.

847
01:08:25,603 --> 01:08:29,523
Our experiences, the times we've had.

848
01:08:30,858 --> 01:08:32,693
Even the bad ones.

849
01:08:34,487 --> 01:08:36,447
It all adds up to my life.

850
01:08:38,532 --> 01:08:39,784
Me too.

851
01:08:46,165 --> 01:08:47,208
Good bye.

852
01:08:56,050 --> 01:08:59,011
You know, I always imagined
a much different ending for us.

853
01:09:03,140 --> 01:09:04,183
Of course you did.

854
01:09:05,518 --> 01:09:08,103
I'd be in a tux, like this.

855
01:09:09,230 --> 01:09:10,981
And a spotlight would come on.

856
01:09:12,066 --> 01:09:16,570
And you'd enter stage right
in a sparkling gown.

857
01:09:20,115 --> 01:09:24,119
[BOTH SINGING IN SPANISH]

858
01:10:54,335 --> 01:10:55,628
Mwah!

859
01:10:55,794 --> 01:10:59,340
Hey, I want to get my shoes back.
Okay?

860
01:10:59,798 --> 01:11:02,509
Oh, yeah, of course.
Your shoes, you got it.

861
01:11:03,802 --> 01:11:06,805
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

862
01:11:24,365 --> 01:11:26,367
[SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN]

863
01:11:32,289 --> 01:11:34,333
Merry Christmas, everybody.

864
01:11:34,500 --> 01:11:35,834
[RAGTIME MUSIC PLAYING
ON SPEAKERS]

865
01:11:36,001 --> 01:11:37,211
Ho-ho-ho, Merry Christmas.

866
01:11:37,503 --> 01:11:40,547
There we go, try some of that.
Merry Christmas, good to see you.

867
01:11:40,714 --> 01:11:42,675
Hi, sweetie, Mwah.

868
01:11:42,841 --> 01:11:44,385
- You made it.
CHARLES: Yes, I did.

869
01:11:44,551 --> 01:11:46,220
BOY: Uncle Charlie.
- Merry Christmas.

870
01:11:46,470 --> 01:11:48,222
Hey, there they are, whoa.

871
01:11:48,389 --> 01:11:52,518
Ugh, barnacles. Aah, help,
I'm being attacked by barnacles.

872
01:11:52,685 --> 01:11:55,145
[GRUNTS THEN CHUCKLES]

873
01:11:55,312 --> 01:11:58,357
Hey, Charles. Mwah, Merry Christmas.

874
01:11:58,524 --> 01:12:00,067
- Merry Christmas, sis.
- Thank you.

875
01:12:00,275 --> 01:12:03,487
For what?
I have fucked up so much recently.

876
01:12:03,654 --> 01:12:06,949
I heard about what you did.
Thank you for sticking up for me.

877
01:12:07,116 --> 01:12:10,035
The cops came looking for you.
I told them your car was stolen.

878
01:12:10,244 --> 01:12:11,286
Oh, quick thinking.

879
01:12:11,453 --> 01:12:13,747
Tomorrow I'll take you to impound
to pick it up.

880
01:12:13,956 --> 01:12:16,208
You're crazy,
but I love you so, so much.

881
01:12:16,375 --> 01:12:18,293
I love you so much.

882
01:12:19,420 --> 01:12:21,964
Is, uh, is Kirby here?

883
01:12:25,592 --> 01:12:28,470
- There they are.
- Charlie. Merry Christmas.

884
01:12:28,679 --> 01:12:31,223
- Oh.
-It's so great to see you two.

885
01:12:32,099 --> 01:12:37,062
Swan, I ran your numbers again.
And things are not as dire as I thought.

886
01:12:37,521 --> 01:12:38,856
So there's hope for me?

887
01:12:40,107 --> 01:12:41,608
There's always hope.

888
01:12:43,277 --> 01:12:44,945
Hear about Karen and I?

889
01:12:45,487 --> 01:12:46,989
Going to Greece for Christmas.

890
01:12:47,156 --> 01:12:50,951
Saul is so sweet.
He put the plane tickets in my cereal box.

891
01:12:52,286 --> 01:12:54,121
SAUL:
What do you think of that?

892
01:12:59,460 --> 01:13:00,794
Merry Christmas, Kirb.

893
01:13:01,587 --> 01:13:02,963
I love you, man.

894
01:13:04,214 --> 01:13:05,924
Happy Hanukkah, Charlie.

895
01:13:06,800 --> 01:13:08,802
I love you too, brother.

896
01:13:09,636 --> 01:13:11,764
[BOTH LAUGH]

897
01:13:11,930 --> 01:13:14,183
- Holy shit.
CHARLES: What?

898
01:13:14,933 --> 01:13:16,185
I think I'm in love.

899
01:13:16,393 --> 01:13:19,772
I just met this girl over there?
I think she's perfect.

900
01:13:19,938 --> 01:13:21,982
- You think she's the one, huh?
- I think she could be.

901
01:13:22,149 --> 01:13:25,486
- That's fantastic.
- Yeah.

902
01:13:25,652 --> 01:13:30,157
Folks, listen up. We have some business
to discuss in the conference room...

903
01:13:30,324 --> 01:13:32,993
...if everyone can please
head in there now, chop chop.

904
01:13:33,619 --> 01:13:34,828
Including you.

905
01:13:35,746 --> 01:13:39,750
I've been asked to present this gift
by the employees of Swan Design...

906
01:13:40,000 --> 01:13:41,960
...to honor a very special person.

907
01:13:42,336 --> 01:13:45,964
To know him is to be
exasperated by him.

908
01:13:46,131 --> 01:13:47,257
[ALL LAUGH]

909
01:13:47,424 --> 01:13:53,472
Ladies and gentlemen,
little Charlie Swan Ill Junior.

910
01:13:53,931 --> 01:13:56,350
Which I guess makes him
Charles Swan IV.

911
01:13:56,517 --> 01:13:58,477
[ALL CHUCKLE]

912
01:14:02,481 --> 01:14:03,524
[ALL LAUGHING]

913
01:15:17,431 --> 01:15:20,601
I have an idea for your album cover,
it just popped in my head.

914
01:15:20,767 --> 01:15:22,352
Yeah? What is it?

915
01:15:22,811 --> 01:15:25,772
It's everything.
Everything plus the kitchen sink.

916
01:16:33,757 --> 01:16:35,759
[SIGHS]

917
01:17:01,952 --> 01:17:03,036
Morning.

918
01:17:05,038 --> 01:17:06,498
Looking good.
How are we doing?

919
01:17:06,915 --> 01:17:08,208
MARNIE:
You have to figure it out.

920
01:17:08,375 --> 01:17:10,127
- Hey. Looking good.
- Excellent.

921
01:17:13,422 --> 01:17:16,258
- Looking sharp. How are you feeling?
- Great. Great.

922
01:17:29,187 --> 01:17:30,230
[ALL CHATTERING]

923
01:18:02,512 --> 01:18:03,764
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

924
01:18:11,355 --> 01:18:14,107
I'm Charlie Sheen
and I play Charles Swan Ill.

925
01:18:14,274 --> 01:18:16,693
I'm Jason Schwartzman
and I play Kirby Star.

926
01:18:16,860 --> 01:18:18,779
I'm Katherine Winnick and I play Ivana.

927
01:18:19,071 --> 01:18:21,281
I'm Bill Murray. I play Saul.

928
01:18:21,448 --> 01:18:23,658
I'm Patricia Arquette. I play Izzy Swan.

929
01:18:23,867 --> 01:18:26,328
I'm Liam Hayes and I wrote the music.

930
01:18:28,789 --> 01:18:31,792
<i>[SINGING]
I'm so happy that you're finally free</i>

931
01:18:32,667 --> 01:18:35,796
<i>You jumped the fence
But you didn't take me</i>

932
01:18:36,588 --> 01:18:39,800
<i>I'm in this jungle here all by myself</i>

933
01:18:40,634 --> 01:18:44,221
<i>I got this song and not much else</i>

934
01:18:44,888 --> 01:18:48,016
<i>Violet voyage on an endless sea</i>

935
01:18:48,767 --> 01:18:51,770
<i>You couldn't stay and I couldn't leave</i>

936
01:18:52,646 --> 01:18:55,982
<i>But if I had to do it all again</i>

937
01:18:56,650 --> 01:18:59,444
<i>I'd love you twice as much
As I did then</i>

938
01:18:59,611 --> 01:19:02,280
<i>So much music</i>

